This paper deals with the concept of equilibrium and quality of service provisioning in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also introduces the concept of effort or cost of satisfaction, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the decentralized algorithm for self-configuring networks, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions transmit power levels and constellation sizes, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
